values:
well. Sunday: i rode in a convertible for the first time. it was incredible. liberating. steph and i, smushed into Chad's little 2 seater, with the top down and the music up loud while he took us for a spin. a very fast spin. hot guy + hot car + loud music + wind in my hair + full of God + best friend + crazy speed = bliss. i honestly want&nbsp;a convertible even more than i want a pickup. which is sayin somethin. cause i REALLY want a pickup.&nbsp;

i have amazing friends. i realized this when i called Zach this afternoon "hey, Zachy... will you do me a favor?" "Yes." wow. its nice to hear that every once in a while. not 'depends on what it is.' or 'maybe' or 'what?'. just 'yes.' so now im up late doing my APWH DBQ. wheeee. but thats okay, cause im taking a break (another one) to update my lj. that i havent updated in a while. so, right... life is quite nice. kind of twisted in the 'im a girl and thereby have no idea WHAT i feel towards WHO right now but its okay cause i love my life in general, and love everyone involved, regardless' sort of way.&nbsp;

i love stephanie claire, my cripple. my sister, my other half, my strength, my comfort... my PSOM. keeper of inside jokes and giver of hugs and wiper of tears and only one who plays with my hair, and always ALWAYS makes time for me. who understands his priorities: God, then CAROLINE. no questions asked. best friends are more than recommended... they're NECESSARY.
